    <section>
        <title>Viewing Concept Timeline Properties</title>
        <section>
            <title>Komet Interface</title>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Journal Interface</title>
            <orderedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>In the tool ribbon at the top of the concept window, click the green Time
                        Travel button. <figure xml:id="TimeTravelButton">
                            <title>Time Travel Button</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Time%20Travel%20Button.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>The Timeline panel opens to the right. Colored lines in the
                        Timeline panel represent different data extensions.</para><figure xml:id="TimelinePanel">
                            <title>Timeline Panel</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Timeline%20Panel.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the three vertical dots on the right to view Timeline settings. You
                        can change which extensions you wish to view in the Timeline panel.</para>
                    <figure xml:id="TimelineSettings">
                            <title>Timeline Settings</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Timeline%20Settings.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the Properties toggle on the right, above the Timeline panel, to
                        enable the Properties panel. <figure xml:id="PropertiesToggle">
                            <title>Properties Toggle</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Properties%20Toggle.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>This opens the Properties panel between the concept details view
                        and the Timeline panel. The Properties panel contains options for the Edit,
                        Hierarchy, History, and Comments views.</para>
                    <figure xml:id="PropertiesPanel">
                        <title>Properties Panel</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="images/Properties%20Panel.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the History view in the Properties panel. The History view shows
                        event details for each event dot on the Timeline extension(s).</para>
                    <figure xml:id="TimelineandHistory">
                            <title>Timeline and History</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Timeline%20and%20History.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>Click the Range toggle below the Properties toggle to enable range
                        selection on the timeline. 
                        <figure xml:id="RangeToggle">
                            <title>Range Toggle</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Range%20Toggle.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>This allows you to select event dots you wish to
                        view within a specific time range. 
                        <figure xml:id="EventsWithinaRange">
                            <title>Events Within a Range</title>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="images/Events%20Within%20a%20Range.png"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </figure>When you define a specific time range,
                        the History view only shows event details for event dots contained within
                        that time range. When an event dot is selected, the dot turns green and the
                        corresponding historical record is outlined red.</para>
                    <figure xml:id="HistoryWithinaRange">
                        <title>History Within a Range</title>
                        <mediaobject>
                            <imageobject>
                                <imagedata fileref="images/History%20Within%20a%20Range.png"/>
                            </imageobject>
                        </mediaobject>
                    </figure>
                </listitem>
                <listitem><para>Click the dropdown at the top of the History view to filter historical records by Concept, Description, and Axiom change events.
                </para><figure xml:id="HistoricalRecordsFilter">
                    <title>Historical Records Filter</title>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="images/Historical%20Records%20Filter.png"/>
                        </imageobject>
                    </mediaobject>
                </figure>
                </listitem>
            </orderedlist>
        </section>
